def speed_kde_plot(col):
    # Plot the first figure and set the size of the figure
    plt.figure(1,figsize=(15,3))
    df[col][df.label == 1].plot(kind='kde')    
    df[col][df.label == 0].plot(kind='kde')
    # sets our legend for our graph.
    plt.legend(('Dangerou Trip', 'Safe Trip'),loc='best') 
    plt.xlabel(col)
# Call the function to plot the distribution plot
speed_kde_plot('Speed')

Define a function that prints out the max, min and median value of a column in df

In [36]:
def min_max_median(column):
    # Display the statistics of the selected column
    print('Min Value of {}: {}'.format(column, df[column].max()))
    print('Max Value of {}: {}'.format(column, df[column].min()))
    print('Median Value of {}: {}'.format(column, df[column].median()))

def dist_plot(first_plot, second_plot):
    # Plot for the figure 1
    plt.figure(1, figsize=(15,5))
    # Add in the first subplot
    plt.subplot(121)
    # Plot for the histogram
    plt.hist(df[first_plot])
    # Do the same for the second subplot
    plt.subplot(122)
    plt.hist(df[second_plot])
    plt.show()
dist_plot('gyro_x','gyro_y')

class ml_models_training:
    # Init the class with 2 properties
    def __init__(self):
        # Store the different classifiers into a property
        self.models = [
            ExtraTreesClassifier(random_state=0),
            DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=2),
            OneVsRestClassifier(RandomForestClassifier(random_state=0)),
            PassiveAggressiveClassifier(random_state=0),
            GaussianNB(),
            SVC(random_state=0),
            LogisticRegression(random_state=0),
            KNeighborsClassifier(),
            RandomForestClassifier(),
            DummyClassifier(random_state=0),
            AdaBoostClassifier(random_state=0),
            BaggingClassifier(random_state=0),
            GradientBoostingClassifier(random_state=0)
        ]
        # Store the names of the classifiers into another property
        self.model_names = [
            'ExtraTreesClassifier', 'DecisionTreeClassifier', 'OneVsRestClassifier',
            'PassiveAggressiveClassifier', 'GaussianNB', 'SVC', 'LogistiRegression',
            'KNeighborsClassifer', 'RandomForestClassifer', 'DummyClassifer',
            'AdaBoostClassifier', 'BaggingClassifier',
            'GradientBoostingClassifier'
        ]
    # Function to train and test to see model scores
    def model_selection(self):
        # Init arrays to store name and scores for training
        name_list = []
        scores_list = []
        training_scores = []
        # Loop through all classifiers
        for model, model_name in zip(self.models, self.model_names):
            # Train the model and append the scores
            model.fit(X_train, y_train)
            name_list.append(model_name)
            scores_list.append(model.score(X_test, y_test))
            training_scores.append(model.score(X_train, y_train))
        # Display the scores in a data frame
        return pd.DataFrame({'Model Names': name_list, 'Model Training Scores': training_scores, 'Model Testing Scores': scores_list})

class GBC_model_tunning:
    # Init the tuning class with 5 properties
    def __init__(self, random_state=0, learning_rate=0.1, n_estimators=100, max_depth=3):
        self.random_state = random_state
        self.learning_rate = learning_rate
        self.n_estimators = n_estimators
        self.max_depth = max_depth
        self.best_score = 0
    # Function to visualize the tuning process
    def visualize_process(self, tmp_score, x, y, title):
        plt.plot(range(len(tmp_score)), tmp_score)
        plt.xlabel(x)
        plt.ylabel(y)
        plt.title(title)
        plt.show()
    # Print out the best tuning scores and their respective values
    def display_best_score(self,parameter_name, score,parameter_val):
        print('Highest Accuracy Score Obtained While Tuning the {}: {}'.format(
            parameter_name, score))
        print('Best {} to obtain the highest score: {}'.format(
            parameter_name, parameter_val))
    # Function to tune random_state
    def tuning_random_state(self, random_state_range):
        tmp_score = []
        # Loop through all random_state passed in
        for rs in random_state_range:
            model = GradientBoostingClassifier(random_state=rs)
            model.fit(X_train, y_train)
            tmp_score.append(model.score(X_test, y_test))
        # Visualize the process
        self.visualize_process(tmp_score, "random_state",
                               'Accuracy', 'Tunning Accuracy for random_state')
        best_score = max(tmp_score)
        best_score_index = tmp_score.index(best_score)
        # Modify properties for the best random_state
        self.random_state = random_state_range[best_score_index]
        # Display the best score
        self.display_best_score('random_state',best_score,self.random_state)
    # Function to tune learning_rate
    def tuning_learning_rate(self, learning_rate_range):
        tmp_score = []
        for lr in learning_rate_range:
            model = GradientBoostingClassifier(
                learning_rate=lr, random_state=self.random_state)
            model.fit(X_train, y_train)
            tmp_score.append(model.score(X_test, y_test))
        self.visualize_process(tmp_score, "learning_rate",
                               'Accuracy', 'Tunning Accuracy for learning_rate')
        best_score = max(tmp_score)
        best_score_index = tmp_score.index(best_score)
        self.learning_rate = learning_rate_range[best_score_index]
        # Display the best score
        self.display_best_score('learning_rate',best_score,self.learning_rate)
    # Function to tune n_estimators
    def tuning_n_estimators(self, n_estimators_range):
        tmp_score = []
        # Loop through all the range passed in
        for ne in n_estimators_range:
            model = GradientBoostingClassifier(
                learning_rate=self.learning_rate, n_estimators=ne, random_state=self.random_state)
            model.fit(X_train, y_train)
            tmp_score.append(model.score(X_test, y_test))
        self.visualize_process(tmp_score, "n_estimators",
                               'Accuracy', 'Tunning Accuracy for n_estimators')
        best_score = max(tmp_score)
        best_score_index = tmp_score.index(best_score)
        self.n_estimators = n_estimators_range[best_score_index]
        # Display the best score
        self.display_best_score('n_estimators',best_score,self.n_estimators)
        self.best_score = best_score

In [153]:
class neural_network_model(model_init):
    # Init the model properties
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.early_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5)
    # Function to set up model
    def setup_model(self,activation='tanh',loss_activation='sigmoid',layers=0,neurons=10,input_neuron=1000):
        self.model.add(Dense(input_neuron, input_shape=(41, ), activation=activation))
        for i in range(layers):
            self.model.add(Dense(neurons, activation='relu'))
            self.model.add(BatchNormalization())
            self.model.add(Dropout(0.2))
        self.model.add(Dense(1, activation=loss_activation))
        self.model.add(Dense(1, activation=loss_activation))
        self.model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy',
                      optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
        return self.model
    # Function to train the model
    def train_model(self):
        # Store history for visualization
        history = self.model.fit(X_train, y_train, validation_data=(X_test, y_test),
                                 epochs=1000, callbacks=[self.early_stopping])
        # Plot for the tuning history
        plt.figure(1, figsize=(20,5))
        plt.subplot(121)
        plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'])
        plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'])
        plt.title('model accuracy')
        plt.ylabel('accuracy')
        plt.xlabel('epoch')
        plt.legend(['train', 'test'], loc='upper left')
        # summarize history for loss
        plt.subplot(122)
        plt.plot(history.history['loss'])
        plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'])
        plt.title('model loss')
        plt.ylabel('loss')
        plt.xlabel('epoch')
        plt.legend(['train', 'test'], loc='upper left')
        plt.show()
    # Evalue the model score
    def evaluate_model(self):
        # Final evaluation of the model
        scores = self.model.evaluate(X_test, y_test, verbose=0)
        print("Loss Error: %.2f%%" % (100-scores[1]*100))
    # Show model summary
    def summarise_model(self):
        self.model.summary()
# Init the instance
base_model = neural_network_model()
